> No rules definition for unit hbox.e1

There hasn't been a unit named `hbox.e1` in ages. Something is wrong with your installation. Please remove the shellmap you are using. If that doesn't help remove everything OpenRA-related and do a clean install.

It looks like you have a modified copy of an old shellmap installed.  Try deleting anything in `~/Library/Application Support/OpenRA/Maps/` (note: the Library directory is hidden by default, so use command-shift-g to open the "go to" sheet and paste that path), and you should find that it works.

Thank you for your support, I found the problem (if was my fault). It seems that when I update old version og OpenRA I combined old and new app bundle (the resulted bundle contained old version of shellmap with links to hbox.e1). Completly removed app bundle and reinstalled.
